iprocal responsibilities and interdependence. For the Siksikaitsitapi, knowledge is experiential, participatory, and ultimately sacred, rather than objective and inert. Rekindling traditional ways of knowing is essential if First Nations people in Canada are to heal and rebuild their communities and cultures. By sharing what she has learned, Betty Bastien hopes to ensure that the next generation of First Nations people will enjoy a future of hope and peace.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 0aSihasapa Indians. 0aSiksika Indians. 0aSiksika language. 0aSiksika philosophy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Indigenous Studies.2bisacsh1 aAlone, Pete Standing, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBastien, Betty, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChief, Duane Mistaken, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKremer, Jurgen W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKremer, Jürgen W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMistaken Chief, Duane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781552382950?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781552382950423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781552382950/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles